🚀 CareerFlow – Job Application Tracker

CareerFlow is a full-stack web application built to help job seekers efficiently track and manage their job applications in one place. This project was created as a practical way to improve my skills in the MERN stack while solving a real-world problem during my job search.

📌 Features
📋 Add job applications with details like:
Company name
Position
Status (Applied, Interview, Rejected, Offer)
Date applied
Location and notes
✏️ Edit existing job entries
❌ Delete job applications
🔄 Real-time UI updates without page refresh
🎯 Status-based color indicators for better visualization

🛠️ Tech Stack

Frontend:
React (with TypeScript)
TailwindCSS / DaisyUI (for UI styling)

Backend:
Node.js
Express.js

Database:
MongoDB (with Mongoose)

📂 Project Structure
careerflow/
├── client/ # Frontend (React)
├── server/ # Backend (Express + MongoDB)
├── README.md

⚙️ Installation & Setup

1. Clone the repository
   git clone https://github.com/your-username/career-flow.git
   cd career-flow

2. Install dependencies
   Client
   cd client
   npm install

Server
cd server
npm install

3. Setup environment variables
   Create a .env file in the server folder:

MONGO_URI=your_mongodb_connection_string
PORT=5000

4. Run the application

Start backend

cd server
npm run dev

Start frontend

cd client
npm run dev

🎯 Purpose
This project was built to:

Practice full-stack development using the MERN stack
Strengthen understanding of CRUD operations
Improve UI/UX design skills
Create a useful tool for managing job applications

